@startuml Inventory and Storage Sequence Diagram
title Machine Detail — Inventory Prefetch + Storage Scan

actor User
participant "HomePresenter" as Presenter
participant "HostResolver" as Resolver
participant "InventoryService" as Inv
participant "DiskUsageService" as Disk
participant "AsyncJob" as Job
participant "RecentConnectionsStore" as Store

User -> Presenter: Select machine row
activate Presenter
Presenter -> Presenter: SelectHost("PC-01")

group Prefetch IP (background)
    Presenter -> Resolver: NeedsResolve("PC-01")?
    Resolver --> Presenter: true (stale / unknown)
    Presenter -> Job: queue Resolve job
    note right of Presenter: CompleteResolve() caches the IP\nand updates the row's reachability dot.
end

group Prefetch inventory (background, if stale)
    Presenter -> Presenter: InventoryIsStale("PC-01")?
    Presenter -> Inv: PrepareInventory("PC-01")
    Inv --> Presenter: worker args (CIM probe script)
    Presenter -> Job: queue Inventory job
end

== PumpJobs(): Inventory job completes ==
Presenter -> Inv: ParseInventory("PC-01")
activate Inv
Inv --> Presenter: MachineInventory (model, battery, disk, uptime)
deactivate Inv
Presenter -> Store: UpsertInventory("PC-01", inv)
Presenter -> Presenter: PopulateDetailCards()
note right of Presenter: InventoryFormat derives battery-health,\ndisk-free and uptime labels (pure, tested).

== On demand ==
User -> Presenter: Click "Storage scan"
Presenter -> Disk: PrepareDiskScan("PC-01")
Disk --> Presenter: worker args (TopN)
Presenter -> Job: queue DiskScan job
note right of Presenter: Worker deploys wiztree64.exe,\nMFT-scans C:, copies folders.json back.

== PumpJobs(): DiskScan job completes ==
Presenter -> Disk: ParseDiskUsage("PC-01")
activate Disk
Disk --> Presenter: DiskUsageReport (ranked folders)
deactivate Disk
Presenter -> Store: UpsertDiskUsage("PC-01", report)
Presenter -> Presenter: RenderBigFolders()
note right of Presenter: DiskUsageTree.BuildNested() nests folders\nby path containment -> TreeView render.
deactivate Presenter
@enduml
